This paper proposes a new neural architecture for text sequence matching, which is a problem commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are often studied in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
